>> title: Shrimp Tacos with Quick Slaw
>> cuisine: Mexican
>> tags: tacos, quick-cook, high-protein
>> servings: 2

-- Light cooking: the shrimp is a 4-minute sauté; the slaw is a 2-minute toss.

Make the slaw first so it can sit: in a #bowl{}, toss @green cabbage{2%cups}(shredded), @lime juice{1%tbsp}, @olive oil{1%tsp}, @fresh cilantro{2%tbsp}(chopped), and @kosher salt{1/4%tsp}. Set aside.

Cook @../components/proteins/garlic-lime-shrimp{8%oz}, or make it fresh now if you didn't prep it.

Warm @corn tortillas{6}(small) by charring them over a gas flame or in a dry #skillet{} until pliable.

Build each taco: a handful of slaw, then 3-4 shrimp.

Drizzle with @../components/sauces/lime-crema{1%tbsp} and add @avocado{1/2}(sliced).

Serve with @lime{1}(cut into wedges).

-- Assembly time: 10 minutes including the sauté
